ld smiles as she holds it near her face along with the doll. An adult hand steadies the jar and its lid. The girl appears comforted and amused, no longer simply lying passively in bed. The scene then returns to the first blonde woman in the red checked dress, now beside the boy again. She looks toward the viewer with a confident, reassuring expression while the boy behind her lies back with his eyes closed or half-closed, looking sleepy. She continues speaking, her glasses still perched on her head, and her expression becomes more earnest. She raises her hand and forms an “OK” sign with thumb and forefinger, holding it beside her face to emphasize her point.\n\nBack in the girl’s room, the woman in green sits beside the child and addresses the viewer while keeping one hand gently at the girl’s neckline. The girl watches her. The woman lifts the dark jar so it is clearly part of what she is discussing, then holds it at chest level. The child, still holding the doll, looks up at her. The woman opens or handles the jar and dips a finger into it. She smiles down at the girl and then begins applying the ointment to the child’s upper chest, just under the ruffled neckline of her nightgown.\n\nA closer view shows the woman’s hand rubbing the ointment in smooth strokes across the little girl’s chest while the girl rests back against the pillows. The doll sits close beside the child, its blonde head and pink dress visible near the girl’s shoulder. As the woman rubs, the girl’s expression softens; she looks calm and increasingly comfortable, lifting her chin slightly and closing her eyes for a moment. The woman’s hand continues the gentle circular and downward motions over the chest area, then the girl relaxes with a faint smile.\n\nThe wider view returns to the woman in green finishing the application and adjusting the girl’s nightgown and blanket. She smiles down at the child, then looks outward again as if explaining the treatment. The girl sits up a little, and the woman 